cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper is primarily focused on the investigation and attribution of cyber-attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed argumentation-based reasoner (ABR) also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG) to analyze and interpret forensic evidence. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for efficient security countermeasures, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the social aspects of cyber-attacks, such as identifying the perpetrator, which is related to the emerging field of cyberpsychology (cs.CY).
